{"header":"<h1>Module <code><span>Symex.Value</span></code></h1>","type":"documentation","uses_katex":false,"breadcrumbs":[{"name":"Index","href":"../../../../index.html","kind":"leaf-page"},{"name":"soteria","href":"../../../index.html","kind":"page"},{"name":"Soteria","href":"../../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"Symex","href":"../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"Value","href":"#","kind":"module"}],"toc":[],"source_anchor":null,"preamble":"<p>This module defines the minimal interface that symbolic values must implement to be used in Soteria's symbolic execution engine.</p>","content":"<div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec module-type anchored\" id=\"module-type-Expr\"><a href=\"#module-type-Expr\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">module</span> <span class=\"keyword\">type</span> <a href=\"module-type-Expr/index.html\">Expr</a></span><span> = <span class=\"keyword\">sig</span> ... <span class=\"keyword\">end</span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p><code>Expr.t</code> describes a <em>syntactic</em> representation of a value of type <code>'a v</code>. Syntactic objects, unlike semantic values, can contain &quot;free&quot; variables and operations such as substitution have meaning.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec module-type anchored\" id=\"module-type-S\"><a href=\"#module-type-S\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">module</span> <span class=\"keyword\">type</span> <a href=\"module-type-S/index.html\">S</a></span><span> = <span class=\"keyword\">sig</span> ... <span class=\"keyword\">end</span></span></code></div></div>"}